JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will not be paying bonuses to its workers this year. The cash-strapped parastatal is due to release its 2017/18 financial results on Monday. READ: Bonus issue stalls Eskom wage discussions Eskom is currently locked in wage negotiations with three trade unions. The NUM has said that the issue of bonus payments is a deal-breaker and it views management’s decision as a declaration of war. The power utility says it simply can’t afford to pay bonuses. #Eskom The @NUM_Media has said that the bonus payment is a “deal breaker” for the wage negotiations and it views the decision by management not to give bonuses as a declaration of war. Eskom says it simply can’t afford to pay bonuses. eNCA